   <question id="q1">
      <body>
         <p>Now use the information you are given and the General Addition Rule to find the desired
               probability, P(smoke is
               detected<?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101108T232822-0500" content=" by the system"?>).</p>
      </body>
      <short_answer id="A"/>
      <part>
         <response input="A" match="*" score="1"/>
         <explanation>
            <p>P(smoke is
                  detected<?oxy_delete author="mmyers" timestamp="20101108T232830-0500" content=" by the system"?>)
                  = P(D or B)</p>
            <p>= P(D) + P(B) - P(D and B)</p>
            <p>= 0.95 + 0.40 - 0.38</p>
            <p>= 0.97</p>
         </explanation>
      </part>
   </question></page>
